cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it studies social interactions within a massive online network. It could also belong to cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it examines the impact of online social networks on college students. Additionally, it could be categorized as cs.SD (Software Development) as it analyzes the usage patterns of a specific social network service. It may also fit under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) as it explores social interactions and behavior within an online network. Finally, it could be classified as cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as it examines the ways in which individuals interact with technology in a social context.
